Can’t wait for RATR this weekend 🏁🏁 @heatwavevisual @4wheelpartsofficial @methodracewheels @bfgoodrichtires @ruggedradios @kchilites @prpseats @knfilters @dynamic_motorsports @evan_weller_racing @trhwiring1 @donny_kerr_at_ecp_powder @motivegear @thejakevelasco @mcneilracinginc @maximausa @fkrodends @jamarperformance @vpracingfuels @moruzzi_race_motors

Well… they say pictures are worth 1000 words..not really sure what to say but we are definitely heart broken, we have spent a lot of time and effort into this truck to get it to where it was and this is something that should not of happened for multiple reasons but @kdm_shock_technologies and I are okay and that’s all that matters. Metal can be replaced, people can’t. After starting side by side with @darren_parsons towards the back of the pack we chased him around the track the entire heat and believe to of finished 2nd for the day but there was a miscommunication with the finish line flagger and their timing trailer and we were sent out on a 5th lap when we should have been done on the 4th..In doing so we caught a slower class vehicle and when we went to make the pass the lane that the other truck had open for us was unexpectedly taken back causing contact and sending the truck into a hard left turn causing us to roll twice. Like I stated there are multiple reasons why this should not have happen and multiple people to point fingers at but that doesn’t do anything progressive. Hopefully this is a learning experience for all involved to pay more attention on the race course and to the racers you have on the course. Definitely a bummer but time to go back to the shop and get to work. After multiple phone calls to the local authorities,  @heatwavevisual finally shipped down the grill that @kendrickperformance gave us. Just wrapped up this Oil Delivery two reel system for National Petroleum.. it was a bit of a challenge given the space constraints under the box and the amount of items that needed to be mounted and plumbed in. The two systems need to be completely separate so there is no cross contamination while delivering product to their customers. I was able to do almost everything in house.. built out the main rack, stand pipe mounts, 2” alumium piping, hi pressure lines, installed the PTO and ran the electrical for the entire system.  It’s always nice to change up the pace of things and build out something like this for a customer. 

Big thanks to @_donk__ and the dudes at #HRP for getting me all the fittings and hose needed for this job and @competitivemetals for supplying all of the metal and alumium needed. 

On to the next one!! 

#isenhouerbrotherspumpsystems @isenhouer_brothers_racing #inlandkenworthelcajon 😎😎

7/11/2023 marks the end of my 11 year 4 month run as a Diesel Mechanic for Inland Kenworth El Cajon. 

When I was hired in 2012 this was a brand new building, there was no concrete poured, no building walls, no tooling, no customers. It was a 100% clean slate for Inland Kenworth to expand and build a name in the East County area. I have had the pleasure to help with building this dealerships reputation and success into what it is today. There has been a lot of good memories made in this building and I have learned way more then I anticipated. From being an entry level mechanic sweeping floors and changing oil to rebuilding engines, alignments, chassis work, basic electrical, troubleshooting, brakes, clutches etc.. I am extremely grateful for the opportunities that the upper management has given me throughout my time there, without them giving me the ability to chase this dream and take as much time off work as I do to go racing and expand Isenhouer Brothers Racing I surely would not be able to be making this next career move. 

As of 7/12/2023 I will be joining @nick_isenhouer at our shop to continue to grow @isenhouer_brothers_racing. It a very big move to make but we are excited and motivated to see where this journey will take us. So if you guys need any fabrication, race car/ prerunner prep, chase trucks, pretty much anything… let us know how we can help. #isenhouerbrothersracing

We have spent a good amount of time completely going through the @cr_racing_team F100. When we got the truck last year we discussed the options and what chris ultimately wanted to do with it.. from there we decided to strip it down to a chassis and go through and upgrade bits and pieces. We put a new 4” @camburgracing housing with 3.25 rear hubs and TT axels, new 2.5” front hubs, @evan_weller_racing 10” rear gear. Had @moruzzi_race_motors go through the engine and freshen it up, @kdm_shock_technologies work his magic on the shocks along with a complete color change. New @prpseats and belts, @fluidlogic_usa water bottles, @powersteeringsolution went through the box, pump and ram. All new @rpiracing hardware along with @fkrodends. Had @ecp_powdercoating coat all the new alumium panels that we built for the rear and sand blast all of the suspension components to coat it with @steelitcoatings. New @kchilites light package. Put the @mcneilracinginc f100 glass on it and had @ds__customs__ wrap it. New @cbrperformanceproducts trans coolers, new @dynamic_motorsports torque converter, had Culhane go through the trans. All new plumping and added spare parts, upper link, alternator, drive shaft, floor jack etc. Then to top it off with a fresh set of @methodracewheels 103 bead locks with new BFG 40s. It’s a pretty neat hot rod now, huge thank you to Chris for giving us this opportunity to work together and build you a truck. Now Off to @norraracing_official!!
